Named for [[w:Henri Louis Le Châtelier|Henri Louis Le Châtelier]]

===Noun===
'''Le Chatelier's [[principle]]'''
#{{chemistry}} A principle that states that if a chemical system at equilibrium experiences a change in concentration, temperature, or total pressure, the equilibrium will shift in order to minimize that change.

